// TAIL_MARKER_CONT_9z8y7x   (this line lives past the 65535-byte boundary, in OpSourceContinued)

// The checks below are order-independent (CHECK-DAG) because the embedded source spans ~1000
// disassembly lines and interleaves the physical positions of the real instructions with the
// embedded copies of these very CHECK directives; a sequential scan cursor is therefore brittle.
// Each pattern is written so only the real instruction (not an embedded escaped-quote copy of a
// CHECK line) can satisfy it.

// The source is embedded via the core OpSource with a File <id> operand and the source text. The
// disassembler renders the multi-line source with real newlines, so match only the opening (no
// closing quote). `%{{[0-9]+}}` is the File <id>; because the embedded copy of this directive
// keeps the literal `%{{[0-9]+}}` text (which cannot match `%[0-9]+`), only the real instruction
// satisfies the pattern.
// CHECK-DAG: OpSource {{Slang|Unknown}} 1 %{{[0-9]+}} "//TEST:SIMPLE

// The source exceeds one SPIR-V string operand, so a real OpSourceContinued is emitted. The
// embedded copies of this directive use an escaped quote, so only the real instruction (unescaped
// quote) matches.
// CHECK-DAG: OpSourceContinued "

// The tail marker lives past the split boundary, so it must survive in the continuation. Anchoring
// to line start (`{{^}}`) targets the real embedded source line, whose text begins at column 0;
// the embedded copy of this CHECK directive begins with `// CHECK-DAG:` and so cannot match.
// CHECK-DAG: {{^}}// TAIL_MARKER_CONT_9z8y7x   (this line lives past

// No NonSemantic extension is used for the source at g1 (the `= OpExtInstImport` prefix
// matches the real instruction, not an embedded copy of this comment).
// CHECK-NOT: = OpExtInstImport "NonSemantic.Shader.DebugInfo.100"

// At -g2 the source rides the NonSemantic DebugSource path, which shares the same UTF-8-safe
// chunker. For this >65535-byte source that means a real DebugSource plus at least one
// DebugSourceContinued. Match the instruction form (`= OpExtInst %void %<id> Debug...`), which an
// embedded copy of a CHECK directive cannot produce.
// CHECK_G2-DAG: {{%[0-9]+}} = OpExtInst %void {{%[0-9]+}} DebugSource
// CHECK_G2-DAG: {{%[0-9]+}} = OpExtInst %void {{%[0-9]+}} DebugSourceContinued
